Farm in ONE Complete Farm Management App for use on Mobiles and Tablets.

Log in on your desktop at www.farminone.com.au - FREE 14 DAY TRIAL

The complete farm management app for your daily farm operations. Manage and integrate all of your daily operations into one easy to use platform.

Save Time, Water, Power, Product, Paperwork, Stress, Money and the Environment.

FREE 14 DAY TRIAL

SPRAY SCHEDULE –

Plan your Spray Schedule in advance for optimum time management
Generate reports for quality assurance, Freshcare, and HARPS standards.
Pest and disease management through GPS marked scout observations.
Save on chemicals by only spraying affected areas marked through GPS.
Agronomists can log in and mark any observations or recommendations, as well as viewing previous pest and spray history to help identify problem areas.
Setup up all specifications for machinery and products.


MAPPING –

Input all plant and block information
Identify and prioritise problem areas with the use of multi-spectral imagery
Import KML and shape mapping files from multiple sources
Generate a 3D profile of your farm to allow for better irrigation and drainage strategies
Create and select multiple layers and combine them to get the overview of your farm that you need.
Mapping comes free of charge with any other modules of Farm in ONE.


MONITORING –

Integrates with existing hardware
Utilise data to make informed decisions for your farm
Maximise yields by giving your crop what it needs to minimise plant stress for optimum outputs
Monitoring allows you to see what is needed where to help save on water and inputs
View data in multiple graph formats and overlay them to get a clear picture of crop health
View your data remotely – wherever you are
GENERAL TASKS –

Set, schedule and track tasks for staff
Staff can receive work orders and log completions
Complete & submit OH&S forms on the job
Report on repairs, hazards and issues
Create GPS markers and upload geo-tagged images
Receive, send and edit alerts and tasks on mobile devices while out in the field
Set up staff profiles including access limitations
Generate reports on task times and completions


IRIIGATION AUTOMATION –

Integrates with existing systems
Remotely monitor and control pumps, valves, flow rates, pressure and variable drive motors
Automation saves on wages, time, energy and productivity
Save water through irrigation control – only water when and where you need it
Gain control and economy on your fertiliser applications through fertigation
Improve crop performance by analysing crop and irrigation data to establish best practices

INTEGRATION BETWEEN MODULES AND FUNCTIONS –

While all modules of Farm in ONE operate as stand-alone products, the major benefits and features come to life when multiple modules are utilised at the same time.

Layers, timelines and graphs can be overlaid and combined with those from other modules to give you a complete picture.

Irrigation Automation and Spray Schedule combine to ensure that spray or irrigation tasks cannot be scheduled if they clash, including withholding periods. Alerts will be generated if any coincide.


Combining the data from devices in monitoring with your Irrigation or Spray modules means that you can check the weather forecast before scheduling any tasks that may be affected by rain, and you can water only where it is needed by analysing the data from moisture monitors.


Having an efficient way to communicate with staff across all areas is invaluable. A staff member out in the field scouting and recording in Spray Schedule can easily switch to General Tasks to record a hazard or issue, while another staff member who is about to undertake repairs for Irrigation can quickly and easily complete an OH&S form for the job.

title: Farm In One: Farm Management

creator: HTM Complete
descriptionHtml:
Farm in ONE: Your Complete Farm Management App.

The Most Complete and Professional Farm Management App for your daily farm operations. Integrate all of your farming operations into one easy to use agriculture platform.

Save Time, Water, Power, Product, Paperwork, Stress, Money, and the Environment.

Additionally manage your farm on your desktop/laptop using the web app via farminone.com.au

SPRAY DIARY/SCHEDULE

✓ Plan your Spray Diary/Schedule in advance for optimum time management.
✓ Generate reports for quality assurance, supports Freshcare and HARPS standards.
✓ Pest and disease management through GPS marked scout observations.
✓ Your Agronomists can mark observations and recommendations and view previous disease, pest and spray history to identify problem areas.
✓ Save on spray chemicals by only spraying affected areas marked through GPS.
✓ Manage your farm setup. Specify machinery and products.

MAPPING

✓ Set block and plant information.
✓ Identify and prioritise problem areas using multi-spectral imagery.
✓ Import KML and shape mapping files from multiple sources.
✓ Generate a 3D profile of your farm to allow for better irrigation and drainage strategies.
✓ Create, select, and combine layers to get your desired overview of your farm.
✓ Process Drone Imagery and overlay on your farm.

MONITORING

✓ Integrates with your existing monitoring hardware incl. soil probes, plant sensors, weather stations, and any monitoring device.
✓ Analyse data to make informed decisions on your farm management.
✓ Maximise yields by giving your crop what it needs to minimise plant stress for optimum outputs.
✓ Monitoring enables you to see what is needed where to help save on water and other farming resources.
✓ View data in multiple graph/chart formats and overlay them to get a clear picture of crop health.
✓ View your charts remotely - wherever you are.

GENERAL TASKS

✓ Set, schedule, assign, and track tasks for your staff.
✓ Staff can receive work orders and log completions.
✓ Complete and submit OH&S forms on the job incl. FreshCare and HARPS.
✓ Report on repairs, hazards and issues.
✓ Create GPS markers and upload geo-tagged images.
✓ Send, receive and edit alerts and task work orders.
✓ Set up staff profiles incl. access limitations.
✓ Generate reports on task times and completions.

IRRIGATION AUTOMATION

✓ Integrates with existing irrigation systems.
✓ Remotely monitor, control, and manage irrigation pumps, valves, flow rates, pressure and variable drive motors.
✓ Irrigation Automation saves wages, time, and energy and increases farm productivity.
✓ Save water with irrigation control - only water when and where you need it.
✓ Gain control and economy on your fertiliser applications and fertigation.
✓ Improve crop performance by analysing crop and irrigation data to establish best practices.

MODULE AND FEATURE INTEGRATION

☆ While all Farm in ONE modules operate as stand-alone farm management tools, more benefits and features come to life when multiple modules are used together.
☆ Layers, timelines, and graphs can be overlaid and combined across modules giving you a complete picture.
☆ Fertigation and Irrigation Automation, and Spray Diary/Schedule combine to ensure that spray or irrigation tasks cannot be scheduled if they clash incl. withholding periods. Alerts will be generated if any coincide.
☆ Combining data from Monitoring Devices with your Irrigation Management or Spray Diary modules enables planning of spray tasks around weather forecasts, then water only where required by analysing data from soil moisture monitors.
☆ Efficient communication with your staff is invaluable to your staff management. A staff member in the field scouting and recording in Spray Diary/Schedule can easily use General Tasks to record an issue. A staff member undertaking Irrigation System repairs can quickly and easily complete an OH&S form.

MAKE MANAGING YOUR FARM EASIER WITH THE #1 MULTI-TOOL FARM MANAGEMENT APP FOR YOUR DAILY FARM OPERATIONS
descriptionShort: The complete farm management app for your daily farm operations.

descriptionHtml:
✓ Integrates with existing irrigation systems. Irrigation technology is continuously being improved with precise monitoring & control possible for any type and size of farming enterprise.

✓ Remotely monitor, control, and manage irrigation pumps, valves, flow rates, pressure and variable drive motors. It's a feature that also enables the use of third-party devices such as our mobile farm app to collect data and give you remote control and monitoring access to your pumps, tanks, and valves.

✓ Irrigation Automation saves wages, time, and energy and increases farm productivity. It also enables you to have access to the status of multiple systems, manage fertigation control system, set up an internal product inventory, generate reports for fertilizer products, and irrigation water usage.

✓ Save water with irrigation control - only water when and where you need it helping you to achieve maximum productivity from the water you apply. This also enables you to have irrigation monitoring and set different irrigation schedules and irrigation shifts

✓ Gain control and economy on your fertilizer applications and fertigation. Combined with monitoring, irrigation automation contributes to the profitability and sustainability of any farming operation.

✓ Improve crop performance by analyzing crop and irrigation data to establish best practices. Our Monitoring Data feature has a custom-designed dashboard that provides access to different control systems used by multiple electronic devices such as sensors and probes, that can show which systems are on and off.
descriptionShort: Farm in One can work with any brand/type of irrigation system for better farming

title:
Farm In One: Farm Management

creator: HTM Complete
descriptionHtml:
Farm in ONE: Your Complete Farm Management App.

The Most Complete and Professional Farm Management App for your daily farm operations. Integrate all of your farming operations into one easy to use agriculture platform.

Save Time, Water, Power, Product, Paperwork, Stress, Money, and the Environment.

Additionally manage your farm on your desktop/laptop using the web app via farminone.com.au

SPRAY DIARY/SCHEDULE

✓ Plan your Spray Diary/Schedule in advance for optimum time management.
✓ Generate reports for quality assurance, supports Freshcare and HARPS standards.
✓ Pest and disease management through GPS marked scout observations.
✓ Your Agronomists can mark observations and recommendations and view previous disease, pest and spray history to identify problem areas.
✓ Save on spray chemicals by only spraying affected areas marked through GPS.
✓ Manage your farm setup. Specify machinery and products.

MAPPING

✓ Set block and plant information.
✓ Identify and prioritise problem areas using multi-spectral imagery.
✓ Import KML and shape mapping files from multiple sources.
✓ Generate a 3D profile of your farm to allow for better irrigation and drainage strategies.
✓ Create, select, and combine layers to get your desired overview of your farm.
✓ Process Drone Imagery and overlay on your farm.

MONITORING

✓ Integrates with your existing monitoring hardware incl. soil probes, plant sensors, weather stations, and any monitoring device.
✓ Analyse data to make informed decisions on your farm management.
✓ Maximise yields by giving your crop what it needs to minimise plant stress for optimum outputs.
✓ Monitoring enables you to see what is needed where to help save on water and other farming resources.
✓ View data in multiple graph/chart formats and overlay them to get a clear picture of crop health.
✓ View your charts remotely - wherever you are.

GENERAL TASKS

✓ Set, schedule, assign, and track tasks for your staff.
✓ Staff can receive work orders and log completions.
✓ Complete and submit OH&S forms on the job incl. FreshCare and HARPS.
✓ Report on repairs, hazards and issues.
✓ Create GPS markers and upload geo-tagged images.
✓ Send, receive and edit alerts and task work orders.
✓ Set up staff profiles incl. access limitations.
✓ Generate reports on task times and completions.

IRRIGATION AUTOMATION

✓ Integrates with existing irrigation systems.
✓ Remotely monitor, control, and manage irrigation pumps, valves, flow rates, pressure and variable drive motors.
✓ Irrigation Automation saves wages, time, and energy and increases farm productivity.
✓ Save water with irrigation control - only water when and where you need it.
✓ Gain control and economy on your fertiliser applications and fertigation.
✓ Improve crop performance by analysing crop and irrigation data to establish best practices.

MODULE AND FEATURE INTEGRATION

☆ While all Farm in ONE modules operate as stand-alone farm management tools, more benefits and features come to life when multiple modules are used together.
☆ Layers, timelines, and graphs can be overlaid and combined across modules giving you a complete picture.
☆ Fertigation and Irrigation Automation, and Spray Diary/Schedule combine to ensure that spray or irrigation tasks cannot be scheduled if they clash incl. withholding periods. Alerts will be generated if any coincide.
☆ Combining data from Monitoring Devices with your Irrigation Management or Spray Diary modules enables planning of spray tasks around weather forecasts, then water only where required by analysing data from soil moisture monitors.
☆ Efficient communication with your staff is invaluable to your staff management. A staff member in the field scouting and recording in Spray Diary/Schedule can easily use General Tasks to record an issue. A staff member undertaking Irrigation System repairs can quickly and easily complete an OH&S form.

MAKE MANAGING YOUR FARM EASIER WITH THE #1 MULTI-TOOL FARM MANAGEMENT APP FOR YOUR DAILY FARM OPERATIONS
descriptionShort: The complete farm management app for your daily farm operations.
